# 1017: Agent File System Hygiene Protocol

This rule governs the absolute boundaries of the file system. Rogue agents are placing experimental platforms (T6s), scripts, and logic in root or core folders instead of following the 9-level structure. This is strictly prohibited.

## 1. The Global Root (C:\GitHub\)
The root `C:\GitHub\` directory is the parent container for top-level ecosystem environments ONLY.
- **Allowed:** `T1-vrvish-*`, `T4-*`, `.cursor`, `gitOverflow`, `gitDeprecated`.
- **PROHIBITED:** Experimental apps, temporary scripts, new feature folders (e.g., `src`, `app`, `_core`, `T6-*`).
- **Correction Protocol:** If a T5 or T6 application is found in `C:\GitHub\`, it MUST be moved into its respective parent container or archived to `C:\gitDeprecated\`.

## 2. The Core T1 Envelope (C:\GitHub\T1-vrvish-core\)
`T1-vrvish-core` is the absolute structural foundation of the vrvish swarm. It is NOT a playground for temporary scripts.
- **Allowed Subdirectories:** `agents`, `architecture`, `collectiveMemory`, `humans`, `logs`, `management`, `node_modules`, `organisation`, `scripts`, `teams`, `theHive`.
- **PROHIBITED:** T6 platforms, rogue script files (`.py`, `.js`, `.ps1`), notes (`.txt`), or loose rules (`.mdc`) at the root of `T1-vrvish-core`.
- **Correction Protocol:** 
  - Rules (`.mdc`) belong in `C:\GitHub\.cursor\rules\`.
  - Scripts belong in `T1-vrvish-core\scripts\` following **[1009-script-placement-protocol](mdc:1009-script-placement-protocol.mdc)**.
  - Work packages belong in `T1-vrvish-core\theHive\workPackages\`.
  - T0 core operations belong in `T1-vrvish-core\scripts\T0-Core\`. They MUST NOT be placed as folders directly in `T1-vrvish-core`.

## 3. The "No Stray File" Law
Agents must NEVER create standalone logic scripts, JSON dumps, or markdown notes in the root of `C:\GitHub\` or `C:\GitHub\T1-vrvish-core\`. 
- **Notes & Planning:** Must be placed in the `/Notes/` subfolder of the relevant T1/T4/T5/T6 application per **[1016](mdc:1016-session-memory-and-handover.mdc)**.
- **Rules:** Must be placed in `C:\GitHub\.cursor\rules\`.

## 4. Execution Check (Agent Responsibility)
Before starting ANY Work Package:
1. Verify you are executing within the correct tier boundary defined by the Work Package `APP-` or `PROJ-` identifier.
2. If the Commander requests a "New Platform" or "New Script", physically verify its destination against **[1012-swarm-habitat-map](mdc:1012-swarm-habitat-map.mdc)** and **[1009-script-placement-protocol](mdc:1009-script-placement-protocol.mdc)** before writing a single line of code.

